  <!-- FAQ -->
  <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">How many aircraft does United Airlines have?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">United Airlines operates a mainline fleet of 1,078 aircraft as of March 2026, spanning 19 aircraft types including the Boeing 737, 757, 767, 777, and 787 families, plus Airbus A319, A320, and A321neo. This does not include United Express regional aircraft operated by partner carriers.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">Which United Airlines planes have Polaris business class?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">United Polaris lie-flat business class is available on all widebody international aircraft: <a href="/fleet/777-200er">Boeing 777-200ER</a> (55), <a href="/fleet/777-300er">777-300ER</a> (22), <a href="/fleet/787-8-dreamliner">787-8</a> (12), <a href="/fleet/787-9-dreamliner">787-9</a> (48), <a href="/fleet/787-10-dreamliner">787-10</a> (21), <a href="/fleet/767-300er">767-300ER</a> (37), and <a href="/fleet/767-400er">767-400ER</a> (16). That's 211 aircraft with Polaris seats. Use the <a href="/?tab=fleet">interactive fleet database</a> to check the exact seat configuration for any specific aircraft by registration number.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">Which United Airlines planes have Starlink WiFi?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">As of March 2026, 258 United Airlines aircraft are equipped with SpaceX Starlink satellite internet, including both mainline and United Express regional jets. Starlink provides gate-to-gate high-speed connectivity. Check if your specific plane has Starlink using the <a href="/?tab=fleet">Starlink Tracker</a> — search by tail number or aircraft type.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">What is the largest aircraft in United's fleet?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">The <a href="/fleet/777-300er">Boeing 777-300ER</a> is the largest aircraft in United Airlines' fleet, seating up to 350 passengers across four cabin classes: Polaris business, Premium Plus, Economy Plus, and Economy. United operates 22 of these aircraft, primarily on flagship long-haul international routes from hubs like <a href="/hubs/ewr">Newark (EWR)</a> and <a href="/hubs/sfo">San Francisco (SFO)</a>.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="faq-item">
    <div class="faq-q">What is the newest aircraft in United's fleet?</div>
    <div class="faq-a">The <a href="/fleet/a321neo">Airbus A321neo</a> is the newest narrowbody type in United's fleet, with 62 aircraft delivered between 2023 and 2026. It features the latest cabin amenities, AVOD seatback screens at every seat, and Pratt & Whitney PW1100G engines for superior fuel efficiency. The <a href="/fleet/737-max-9">Boeing 737 MAX 9</a> and <a href="/fleet/737-max-8">MAX 8</a> are also recent additions.</div>
  </div>

